        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "Single Line Comments",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Single line comments start with // .",
      "html": "<p>Single line comments start with <code>//</code>.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Any text between // and the end of the line will be ignored (will not be executed).",
      "html": "<p>Any text between <code>//</code> and the end of the line will be ignored (will not be executed).</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "You can also use # for single line comments, but in this tutorial we will use // .",
      "html": "<p>You can also use <code>#</code> for single line comments,\nbut in this tutorial we will use <code>//</code>.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "The following examples uses a single-line comment as an explanation:",
      "html": "<p>The following examples uses a single-line comment as an explanation:</p>"
